cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for control of a robotic arm, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of model-based policy search and optimal control methods suggests it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on control of a robotic arm suggests it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of PID controllers and optimal control methods suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
